-----------------------------------
HOW TO GET YOUR MID AND MERCHANT KEY
-----------------------------------
Both staging and production credentials are issued from the Paytm dashboard:
  https://dashboard.paytmpayments.com/next/apikeys

For Staging (sandbox / test data):
  1. Open the link above and sign in.
  2. You land on the "Test API Details" tab by default.
  3. Click "Generate Now" — your staging MID and Merchant Key appear instantly.
  4. Copy both into the staging block below.

For Production (live payments):
  1. Same URL, switch to the "Production API Details" tab.
  2. Production keys are issued only after KYC + account activation are
     complete. If the tab shows nothing, finish onboarding on the dashboard
     first or contact your Paytm KAM.
  3. Copy MID and Merchant Key into the production block below.

Always wrap the Merchant Key in double quotes — it can contain '#', '@', '$',
which an unquoted .env value would treat as a comment / shell metacharacter.

-----------------------------------
For Staging Environment
-----------------------------------
PAYTM_ENVIRONMENT=staging
PAYTM_MID=
PAYTM_MERCHANT_KEY=" "
PAYTM_WEBSITE_NAME=WEBSTAGING
PAYTM_CALLBACK_BASE=


-----------------------------------
For Production Environment
-----------------------------------
PAYTM_ENVIRONMENT=production
PAYTM_MID=
PAYTM_MERCHANT_KEY=" "
PAYTM_WEBSITE_NAME=DEFAULT
PAYTM_CALLBACK_BASE=


-----------------------------------
FIELD DESCRIPTIONS
-----------------------------------
PAYTM_ENVIRONMENT: Defines whether you are using test (staging) or live (production) environment.
PAYTM_MID: Your unique Merchant ID provided by Paytm for processing payments.
PAYTM_MERCHANT_KEY: Secret key used to secure transactions and generate checksums. Keep this confidential and never expose it publicly.
PAYTM_WEBSITE_NAME: Identifies the environment setup. Use WEBSTAGING for testing and DEFAULT for production.
PAYTM_CALLBACK_BASE: The base URL where Paytm sends payment response after checkout. This should be a publicly accessible URL to receive transaction status.

-----------------------------------
IMPORTANT NOTES
-----------------------------------
- Use staging environment for testing integrations.
- Switch to production only after successful testing.
- Ensure callback URL is correct to avoid missing payment updates.
- Never expose Merchant Key in frontend or public repositories.
